Main Hall
3
The main hall of the royal castle loomed before everyone, its towering stone walls and vaulted ceilings creating an
ominous sense of grandeur. The air was thick with the scent of burning candles and one can see old paintings obscured by
the flickering shadows cast by the torches lining the walls.
10
